# STA-MIL Implementation Walkthrough

## What Was Built

**STA-MIL** (Spatio-Temporal Attention MIL) — a novel transformer model for weakly supervised shoplifting detection on UCF-Crime.

### Novel Contributions (vs. SOTA)
| Feature | Existing SOTA | STA-MIL |
|---------|--------------|---------|
| Backbone | C3D / ResNet-50 | **VideoMAE-Base** |
| Architecture | Single-stream transformer | **Dual-branch cross-attention** |
| Temporal modeling | Fixed-scale pooling | **Multi-scale (3 temporal scales)** |
| MIL loss | Standard ranking | **Contrastive + hard negative mining** |
| Motion features | Optical flow (expensive) | **Gradient temporal differences** |

---

## Project Structure (Created)

```
Shoplifting Antigravity/
├── configs/config.yaml              ← All hyperparameters
├── src/
│   ├── data/
│   │   ├── extract_features.py     ← VideoMAE-Base feature extraction
│   │   └── dataset.py              ← UCF-Crime MIL dataset loader
│   ├── models/
│   │   ├── sta_mil.py              ← Core STA-MIL model
│   │   └── losses.py               ← Contrastive MIL loss
│   ├── utils/
│   │   ├── logger.py               ← TensorBoard + console logging
│   │   └── metrics.py              ← AUC-ROC + SOTA comparison
│   ├── train.py                    ← Full training loop
│   ├── evaluate.py                 ← Evaluation + per-category AUC
│   └── visualize.py                ← Anomaly score timeline plots
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## What to Run (Step by Step)

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. Extract VideoMAE features (~3–5 min per 100 videos)
```bash
python src/data/extract_features.py --config configs/config.yaml --split all
```

### 3. Run a quick dry-run test (validates full pipeline)
```bash
python src/train.py --config configs/config.yaml --dry_run --epochs 2
```

### 4. Train the full model
```bash
python src/train.py --config configs/config.yaml
```

Monitor with TensorBoard:
```bash
tensorboard --logdir logs/
```

### 5. Evaluate
```bash
python src/evaluate.py --config configs/config.yaml --checkpoint checkpoints/best_model.pth
```

### 6. Visualize
```bash
python src/visualize.py --category Shoplifting --n_videos 5 --compare
```

---

## Architecture Diagram (for research paper)

```
Input: VideoMAE features [B, T=32, D=768]
               │
       ┌───────┴───────┐
       │               │
  Spatial          Temporal Branch
  Transformer     (motion diff +
  (4-layer         4-layer xformer)
  self-attn)
       │               │
       └───────┬───────┘
               │
    Bidirectional Cross-Attention
    Fusion (2 layers, 8 heads)
               │
    Multi-Scale Temporal Pooling
    • Scale 1: global (1 group)
    • Scale 2: mid (√T groups)
    • Scale 3: local (T groups)
               │
    MIL Scoring Head (2-layer MLP)
               │
    Scores [B, T] ∈ [0,1]
```

