## SOTA Targets

| Method | AUC |
|--------|-----|
| Sultani et al. (C3D) | 75.41% |
| RTFM | 84.30% |
| MGFN | 85.46% |
| TEF-VAD | 86.40% |
| REWARD | 86.94% |
| **STA-MIL (target)** | **≥ 87%** |

---

## For the Research Paper

Key claims to back with experiments:
1. **Dual-branch fusion** outperforms single-stream (ablation: remove temporal branch)
2. **Multi-scale pooling** helps catch both brief and extended shoplifting acts
3. **Hard negative mining** in loss improves AUC vs. standard ranking loss
4. **VideoMAE** features are superior to C3D/I3D for anomaly detection
